node.text: #APOLLONEWS: @BlueThePlay comes to our historic stage starting April 27! Directed by Phylicia Rashad, written by Charles Randolph-Wright, with music by @nonahendryx, the cast includes Tony Award and Emmy Award-winning #ApolloLegend @leslieuggams1, Emmy Award-winning @mslynnwhitfield and many more!  The new production will begin previews on April 27, with a formal opening night set for May 10 and run through Aug. 16. (📸: Emilio Madrid-Kuser)

It was a day fit for #queens!! The annual #DiningWithTheDivas Benefit Luncheon was our most successful to date, bringing together a room of powerful and dynamic women in support of the #Apollo’s education and community programs! Chaired by @cookiesfablife, Joan Haffenreffer and @borden.terri, this year’s event was hosted by #CondolaRashad @dolabunny and featured empowering remarks on activism from #NikoleHannahJones @colabird76, @bethannhardison and #NadjaBellanWhite with a guest performance by @amberskyez!  Our thanks to the chairs, host committee and the attendees who make this annual event a #galentines we look forward to year in and year out! ❤️💕❤️
📸 @shaharazran1

#ONELOVE! Today we salute the 75th year of @BobMarley’s global legacy! In the Fall of 1979, #BobMarley and the Wailers made their #Apollo debut with a sold-out seven show run!
⁠⠀
These performances were special because #Harlem was brimming with the early flames of the #Rastafari Movement and Marley’s concert run was his attempt to spread the message of Pan-Africanism and global black unity to black communities in North America.💚💛❤️⁠⠀
.⁠⠀

Celebrating #BlackHistoryMonth! For the past 13 years, @ApolloEdHarlem has partnered with PS 154 in #Harlem to collect oral histories from members of the Significant Elders of Harlem, a community outreach group focused on empowering and passing down knowledge to younger generations. This episode of “Stories Our Elders Tell Us” features the late Harold "Mr. G" Gallop, who sat down with 4th and 5th-grade students to share his memories of the Apollo, his birthplace of #Harlem and more! 🔗in BIO!⁠

COLLEGE STUDENTS with a serious interest in working behind-the-scenes in preserving cultural history: APPLY for a PAID 12-week summer internship with the Apollo Theater Archives! 🔗IN BIO🔗 📌You’ll help us organize, catalog, and digitize the Apollo’s exclusive collection of video, audio, photographs, memorabilia, and more. The opportunity is open to undergraduates, graduate students, and recent graduates. 📌This program is generously sponsored by The Robert Frederick Smith Fund for the Digitization and Curation of African American History! 📌Hurry. The deadline is Saturday, FEBRUARY 15th! #apolloarchives

It’s the first thing in my life. Go to bed thinking about it and wake up thinking about it. That’s all I live for.” - #MilesDavis • Kick off #BlackHistoryMonth with a FREE advance screening of the documentary “Miles Davis: Birth of the Cool” THIS SATURDAY 2/1 at the #ApolloOpenHouse!.
♦️ After the screening, the film’s director Stanley Nelson, legendary producer James Mtume, rising jazz superstars Keyon Harrold, Angeleisha  @trumpetessa Rogers, and Miles Davis’ nephew, drummer @nefofmiles will join moderator @wbgojazz host Michael Hill for a lively discussion about the jazz legend’s legacy.
♦️...plus! On the Apollo soundstage, we've got activities, storytelling and award-winning film screenings just for kids ages 3+!! ♦️Reserve your spot today: http://bit.ly/ApolloOpenHouse20

A legend has left us!! The Apollo is saddened by the devastating loss of #KobeBryant, his young daughter #Gianna, their friends and their pilot. Let’s continue to send thoughts and prayers of comfort to the families during this heartbreaking time. 💔
Today, we celebrate ✨86 YEARS✨as the SOUL of AMERICAN CULTURE.
